    "collapsible_tabs_UDrTRf": {
      "type": "collapsible-tabs",
      "blocks": {
        "content_aq3BG8": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "What is a GVM upgrade and why do I need one?",
            "content": "<p>Gross Vehicle Mass (GVM) is the maximum your [VEHICLE] can legally weigh when fully loaded—including the truck, passengers, fuel, accessories (like bull bars and canopies), and tow ball weight. If you are towing heavy or building a touring rig, the factory payload gets eaten up fast. Our GVM upgrades legally increase this limit so you can carry your gear without voiding your insurance or risking hefty fines.</p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_97RYwd": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "What does \"Pre-Rego\" and \"SSM Approval\" mean?",
            "content": "<p>SSM stands for Second Stage of Manufacture. When we upgrade your truck <em>before</em> it is registered for the very first time (Pre-Rego), the federal government recognizes ORI as the secondary manufacturer. This means your massive lift, larger tyres, and upgraded GVM are baked into the truck's federal compliance plate. It is 100% legal to drive and insure in every state and territory in Australia.<br/><br/></p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_k7yrdM": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "Will upgrading my GVM reduce my towing capacity?",
            "content": "<p>Not with an ORI package. Some GVM upgrades force you to sacrifice towing capacity to carry more weight in the tub. Our [VEHICLE] packages retain your factory 12,474kg GCM (Gross Combination Mass), meaning you keep your full 4.5T braked towing capacity while maximizing your truck's payload.</p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_xFACmJ": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "What does the NB1 to NB2 category upgrade mean?",
            "content": "<p>By federal standards, NB1 vehicles are \"Light Goods Vehicles\" (under 4.5 tonnes). Our SSM packages legally reclassify your [VEHICLE] as an NB2 \"Medium Goods Vehicle\" (over 4.5 tonnes). This reclassification is the secret to legally unlocking that massive 5500kg–6000kg GVM.</p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_rQQeBN": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "Are 35-inch and 37-inch tyres actually legal on these builds?",
            "content": "<p>Yes! If done Pre-Rego through our Stage 4, 5, 6, or 6.5 SSM packages, the larger tyre sizes are federally engineered and certified as part of the build. No state-based engineering headaches—just turn the key and drive your monster truck legally anywhere in the country.</p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        }
      },
